 The South African National Roads Agency SOC Ltd (SANRAL) would like to notify travellers that blasting is scheduled to take place between Middelburg and Carlton Heights on Wednesday 23 November and again Friday, 25 November 2016 at 3pm. On Wednesday, 23 November, the blast will take place approximately 13.5 km outside Middelburg on the Carlton Heights side. On Friday, 25 November the blast will take place 16.5 km outside Middelburg on the Carlton Heights side. The road will be closed for approximately 15 minutes during the blast. “Motorists are asked to plan their trips accordingly and to use caution when making use of the road,” said Mbulelo Peterson, SANRAL Southern Region Manager. SANRAL apologises for any inconvenience caused. 